1
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,799
Koharu.

2
00:00:25,799 --> 00:00:28,160
Hey, Koharu!

3
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:30,030
Can you hear me?

4
00:00:31,940 --> 00:00:33,530
Koharu!

5
00:00:34,790 --> 00:00:38,016
- Koharu!
- No family past this point.

6
00:01:33,537 --> 00:01:38,147
[Episode 4]

7
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,540
Koharu.

8
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:56,490
Koharu?

9
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,040
Mom?

10
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:05,060
Thank goodness...

11
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,000
Oh, Koharu...

12
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,170
Come in.

13
00:02:28,390 --> 00:02:32,100
Koharu, it's Miura.

14
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:38,640
Can we talk for a bit?

15
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,450
Is Koharu not here yet?

16
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,920
Koharu.

17
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:25,260
Kakeru?

18
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,440
Yeah...

19
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:36,390
When you didn't come on time,
I thought something happened.

20
00:03:37,975 --> 00:03:40,020
Sorry for the trouble.

21
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,080
No, not at all.

22
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:47,920
Thanks for the other day.

23
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,560
Huh?

24
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,720
The fireworks.

25
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:55,860
Oh, right.

26
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,090
Let's try again sometime.

27
00:04:00,896 --> 00:04:02,376
Yeah, sure.

28
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,570
Next time.

29
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,720
Kakeru, are you wearing a suit?

30
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:17,410
Huh?

31
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:21,110
The rustling sound of your clothes
is different.

32
00:04:22,505 --> 00:04:24,180
That's impressive.

33
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:26,400
I'm heading back to my hometown now.

34
00:04:27,685 --> 00:04:30,610
A third-year memorial. Today, for a friend.

35
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:34,970
A friend?

36
00:04:36,245 --> 00:04:37,680
Yeah.

37
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:40,740
He passed in an accident
when I was in high school.

38
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,800
I see.

39
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,430
He was my best friend.

40
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:52,720
Since it's painful to remember,

41
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:57,770
I couldn't bring myself to go back
for a long time.

42
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:05,160
But I've decided to face it properly.

43
00:05:06,865 --> 00:05:09,240
It's thanks to you.

44
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,330
Huh?

45
00:05:10,970 --> 00:05:15,700
I want to learn from your positivity.

46
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:24,700
Oh, right.

47
00:05:26,385 --> 00:05:29,550
Can I take a video?

48
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:30,730
Huh, why?

49
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:35,700
I want to capture bits of my daily life.

50
00:05:38,470 --> 00:05:40,130
Even if I can't see,

51
00:05:40,896 --> 00:05:45,220
hearing your voice or sounds from that moment

52
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:47,056
can remind me of those times.

53
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:53,360
Why don't you record something too?

54
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,630
Like what?

55
00:05:56,470 --> 00:06:01,510
I want to know
what kind of place you grew up in.

56
00:06:07,335 --> 00:06:09,620
Kakeru, sorry to keep you waiting.

57
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,770
Are you ready?

58
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:11,830
Yeah.

59
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:12,940
Yuuko?

60
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:15,570
Yeah, I have to go, too.

61
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:17,020
I see.

62
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:18,435
I'll be off then.

63
00:06:18,435 --> 00:06:21,405
See you later, Koharu.

64
00:06:21,405 --> 00:06:22,405
Okay.

65
00:06:23,645 --> 00:06:25,580
I'll walk you to the gate.

66
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,550
Are you sure?

67
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:28,885
Why not? It's fine.

68
00:06:28,885 --> 00:06:31,135
- You don't have to.
- Why?

69
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:43,110
Nothing's changed.

70
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,680
Yeah.

71
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:02,823
<i>♪ That's why I'll sing ♪</i>

72
00:07:02,823 --> 00:07:04,598
I can't focus at all.

73
00:07:04,598 --> 00:07:06,618
Then do it at your own place.

74
00:07:08,115 --> 00:07:10,850
Must be nice. You're already in music school.

75
00:07:10,850 --> 00:07:12,520
- Haruto!
- I'm here.

76
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,855
Haruto, go deliver the newsletters.

77
00:07:14,855 --> 00:07:15,865
Got it.

78
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:20,190
Hey, should I grab some snacks while I'm out?

79
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,770
What's good?

80
00:07:21,770 --> 00:07:23,550
Curry bread from Mino Bakery.

81
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:24,680
That's far.

82
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,885
You can use my bike.

83
00:07:26,885 --> 00:07:29,935
All right. Make sure you study, okay?

84
00:07:32,635 --> 00:07:37,060
<i>That was our last conversation.</i>

85
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,870
Auntie?

86
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:57,760
Even if you go to Tokyo,

87
00:07:59,290 --> 00:08:01,750
don't forget about Haruto, okay?

88
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,360
That day,

89
00:08:07,130 --> 00:08:09,590
if I hadn't lent him my bike,

90
00:08:10,980 --> 00:08:13,370
Haruto might still be alive.

91
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:18,380
Auntie could probably...

92
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,850
still smile every day.

93
00:08:24,145 --> 00:08:29,250
When I overslept big time
for my last middle school competition,

94
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:33,292
you saw me running
and lent me your bike, remember?

95
00:08:33,292 --> 00:08:34,972
So what?

96
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:39,400
I'm saying your bike saved someone, too.

97
00:08:40,950 --> 00:08:42,400
You're fine.

98
00:09:08,570 --> 00:09:13,560
[Saeki Music School for Children and Adults]

99
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:32,348
- Please take care of yourself.
- Thank you.

100
00:09:32,348 --> 00:09:35,373
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

101
00:09:40,873 --> 00:09:42,752
Did you come by bus from the station?

102
00:09:42,752 --> 00:09:45,130
Yes. It was quick.

103
00:09:49,173 --> 00:09:54,000
You know, that bus is closing down soon.

104
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:56,415
What? Really?

105
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,070
It'll be inconvenient.

106
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:02,250
But also, I'll miss it.

107
00:10:03,220 --> 00:10:04,220
Huh?

108
00:10:05,490 --> 00:10:09,310
Doesn't it feel like we're being forgotten?

109
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:14,210
Even though we're still here.

110
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,510
Yeah.

111
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,360
Can I sit with you?

112
00:10:35,236 --> 00:10:39,096
Have you been playing the piano lately?

113
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:45,190
You used to play every day
with Haruto, right?

114
00:10:47,810 --> 00:10:50,070
I can't bring myself to.

115
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:54,340
Enjoying it alone feels wrong.

116
00:10:59,035 --> 00:11:04,370
You should come back once in a while
and visit Haruto, okay?

117
00:11:08,466 --> 00:11:10,166
Isn't it okay to...

118
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:13,120
enjoy yourself?

119
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:27,260
Someone I know from college...

120
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:30,580
used to play the piano, too.

121
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,490
But...

122
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:37,290
an illness took her sight.

123
00:11:38,357 --> 00:11:42,257
Now, she can't play like before.

124
00:11:43,924 --> 00:11:45,207
Even so...

125
00:11:47,846 --> 00:11:50,516
she can still play because of her memories.

126
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:57,330
No matter how painful those memories are.

127
00:11:58,218 --> 00:12:03,358
Because of them, she's able to go on living.

128
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:09,870
That person must be struggling, too.

129
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,050
But...

130
00:12:15,970 --> 00:12:17,580
she's enjoying life.

131
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:25,570
I think human emotions...

132
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:29,150
aren't just one thing.

133
00:12:31,940 --> 00:12:34,210
You can smile while feeling sad.

134
00:12:35,950 --> 00:12:37,250
And surely,

135
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:41,710
you can move forward even with regrets.

136
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:53,450
Losing something
doesn't mean you lose everything.

137
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:58,370
So,

138
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:01,490
right now, in this moment,

139
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:05,463
I still want to cherish...

140
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:10,380
everyone around me.

141
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:18,120
That includes you and Haruto.

142
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:35,840
I'm glad...

143
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:40,370
I could see you today.

144
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,140
I'll come again.

145
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:59,120
Thanks for coming with me.

146
00:14:00,070 --> 00:14:01,720
No problem.

147
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,510
Um...

148
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:11,610
You've always been worried about me, huh?

149
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:17,466
I'm glad I came today.

150
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:25,650
That story about the piano.

151
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:28,680
It was Koharu, right?

152
00:14:31,940 --> 00:14:32,940
Yeah.

153
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,580
Then you should be thanking her instead.

154
00:14:45,285 --> 00:14:46,940
Huh?

155
00:14:46,940 --> 00:14:48,750
I'm fine now.

156
00:14:49,890 --> 00:14:54,210
If you're moving forward, Kakeru,
that's enough for me.

157
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:57,535
If you ever feel like looking back,
you're always welcome.

158
00:14:57,535 --> 00:14:59,015
What do you mean?

159
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:05,230
The direction you're moving toward.
Koharu's there, isn't she?

160
00:15:16,395 --> 00:15:19,600
I'm gonna go visit my parents now. See you.

161
00:15:37,307 --> 00:15:38,707
Um,

162
00:15:39,510 --> 00:15:40,820
Koharu.

163
00:15:42,110 --> 00:15:44,480
Here's the video I promised you.

164
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:48,840
It's boring and rural,

165
00:15:49,915 --> 00:15:51,960
but this is my hometown.

166
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:54,430
Why did I start speaking so formally?

167
00:16:00,204 --> 00:16:03,549
A train. Two cars long.

168
00:16:04,415 --> 00:16:08,590
When I was a kid,
I used to wave at trains a lot.

169
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,850
I wonder why.

170
00:16:12,530 --> 00:16:13,990
A reddish-brown bird.

171
00:16:14,930 --> 00:16:16,820
I think it's a...

172
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,120
shrike?

173
00:16:20,690 --> 00:16:21,960
A shrike?

174
00:16:23,915 --> 00:16:30,250
Haruto, my friend, loved birds.

175
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,720
He taught me about them.

176
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:35,300
After Haruto was gone,

177
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:40,040
I was scared of feeling happy.

178
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:46,010
Caring deeply for anyone...

179
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:51,690
or being remembered by people...

180
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:54,690
I'd avoid it.

181
00:16:55,970 --> 00:17:01,230
Otherwise, it hurts too much
when someone leaves.

182
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,040
But,

183
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:13,090
spending time with you, Koharu...

184
00:17:15,370 --> 00:17:17,440
<i>little by little...</i>

185
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:25,840
<i>my once colorless routine bloomed with color.</i>

186
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:31,870
Of course, I still don't know
much about you, Koharu.

187
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:38,980
There's probably a lot about you
I don't know yet.

188
00:17:42,820 --> 00:17:43,960
But...

189
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:48,220
I can learn from now on.

190
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:53,400
I just need to spend more time with you.

191
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:09,250
I won't let the fear of losing someone
hold me back any longer.

192
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:13,450
The sounds of this town,

193
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:16,460
the birds chirping,

194
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,180
the train running...

195
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,540
With all these sounds,

196
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:29,600
I want you to hear what I'm about to say.

197
00:18:41,525 --> 00:18:45,130
I like you, Koharu.

198
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:50,050
If it's okay,

199
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:54,170
I'd like to be with you from now on.

200
00:19:15,235 --> 00:19:18,040
<i>A week passed after that,</i>

201
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,890
<i>then two weeks...</i>

202
00:19:24,990 --> 00:19:26,710
<i>And there was no reply.</i>

203
00:19:28,715 --> 00:19:31,640
Um, in the cultural anthropology fieldwork,

204
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:34,750
at uncharted lands where the subjects live,

205
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:38,750
you find an informant
who will aid in your research,

206
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:42,240
living with them for a long time
to learn about their culture and...

207
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:45,805
I wonder where Koharu is.

208
00:19:45,805 --> 00:19:47,410
Yeah.

209
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:49,300
No contact, right?

210
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:57,620
It might be my fault.

211
00:19:58,480 --> 00:19:59,800
What do you mean?

212
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:04,530
I told Koharu how I feel.

213
00:20:10,450 --> 00:20:13,100
Stupid, that's not a reason to skip school.

214
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:16,610
I'll go to her place after class today.

215
00:20:17,693 --> 00:20:19,578
I'll come, too.

216
00:20:19,578 --> 00:20:20,920
Yuuko! Kakeru!

217
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,510
I found Koharu!

218
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:24,490
- Where?
- She's at Aoba Hospital.

219
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:26,275
The hospital? Why?

220
00:20:26,275 --> 00:20:28,055
I don't know.

221
00:20:48,095 --> 00:20:49,340
Excuse me!

222
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:52,790
Um, is Koharu Fuyutsuki here?

223
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:53,740
Huh?

224
00:20:53,740 --> 00:20:55,725
Koharu Fuyutsuki.

225
00:20:55,725 --> 00:20:57,985
Are you family?

226
00:20:59,035 --> 00:21:01,550
No, but...

227
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:05,200
I'm sorry, I'm not allowed
to disclose that information.

228
00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:15,900
Ophthalmology...

229
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:14,370
Koharu...

230
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:27,790
Thank goodness.

231
00:22:32,675 --> 00:22:35,435
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

232
00:22:48,010 --> 00:22:49,290
Koharu.

233
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:55,970
I was worried since I couldn't reach you.

234
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:00,290
Um...

235
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,740
Are you okay?

236
00:23:12,420 --> 00:23:15,920
Sorry, um...

237
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,000
Oh.

238
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:20,350
I'm Kakeru.

239
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,600
Kakeru?

240
00:23:32,126 --> 00:23:34,966
Have we met somewhere before?

241
00:23:36,586 --> 00:23:37,726
Huh?

242
00:23:45,634 --> 00:23:50,150
The medication can sometimes
cloud her memory.

243
00:23:50,150 --> 00:23:54,940
Does that mean
all the time we spent together is gone?

244
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:58,105
Looks like Koharu doesn't remember us at all.

245
00:23:58,105 --> 00:23:59,856
It's okay if she can't remember.
